I have the actual root cause now: under the full default synthetic config, the representative sampler picks a test-positive graph whose positive edges rank below a pile of negatives. The smoke split is deterministic, but it’s still a bad sanity benchmark. I’m searching the positive-seed pool for a deterministic disjoint assignment that actually reflects learnability under the real config.
